definitions.definition: To rule over ; to govern or determine by superior authority .
To rule or determine in a contrary way; to decide against ; to abrogate or alter .
To nullify a previous ruling by a higher power .
examples: The line judge signalled the ball was in, but this was overruled by the umpire.

definitions.definition: To dismiss or throw out (a protest or objection ) at a court .

main_definition: ( transitive ) To rule over ; to govern or determine by superior authority .
